         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">PROTECTION OF NATIVE BIRDS ¶ My Dear Baron ¶ , — Will you permit me to express my great satisfaction that you are giving your valuable aid and influence to the protection of ¶  ¶ the ¶  ¶ insectivorou...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.11.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Verdon</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. For the published text given here, see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">The Victorian n</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">aturalist</seg>, vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>8, no. 8, December 1891, p. 127.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The letter is introduced: '[The following letter from Sir George Verdon has been forwarded to us by Baron von Mueller for Publication. —<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ed</seg>.]'.</p>
               </note>PROTECTION OF NATIVE BIRDS</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">My Dear Baron</seg>, — Will you permit me to express my great satisfaction that you are giving your valuable aid and influence to the protection of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>insectivorous birds?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Verdon is responding to the following report included in the account of the meeting of the Field Naturalists' Club<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>held on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>16 November 1891, published on p. 113 of the same issue of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victo</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">rian n</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">aturalist</seg>: 'Baron von Mueller, one of the patrons of the club, was accorded a hearty welcome when he rose to advocate the protection of insectivorous and native birds. He thought that this object could be attained not only by putting a comparatively heavy tax upon guns and a great strictness in carrying out the present laws, but rather, perhaps, by the initiation of some scheme which would enlist the sympathy and co-operation of all persons interested in the subject. To this end Baron von Mueller advocated the use of a distinctive badge to be worn by members if such a union were ever inaugurated.'</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The magpies in the Macedon district<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have been nearly exterminated by the poisoned wheat laid down for rabbits. It is quite useless there for that purpose; but it has killed a vast number of the native birds,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which do far more good in destroying insects than the rabbits do harm. It may be of use to you to know this, and so I trouble you with the information.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr Plummer, of Gisborne,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Andrew Plummer?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>informs me that,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>near his house, he found fifteen magpies dead in 150 yards. — I am always, my dear Baron, yours most sincerely,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">GEORGE VERDON.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Club, 24th November, 1891.</p>
         </div>
